<TITLE> Saber no longer political secy to Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 03 (bdnews24.com)Sheikh Hasina on Saturday effectively fired Saber Hossain Chowdhury as her political secretary as the Awami League "abolished" the post. Chowdhury, one of the party's organising secretaries and a former deputy minister, was made political secretary to the party president after the 2001 election debacle. But after the declaration of the state of emergency on Jan 11, 2007, the businessman-politician played rather a subdued role while still formally being in the job. A terse, one-sentence party press release, signed by press secretary Abul Kalam Azad, said Saturday night: "The Awami League president, the Honourable Sheikh Hasina has abolished the post of her political secretary." Saber Chowdhury, however, won the Dhaka-9 seat on the AL ticket in the Dec 29 election. bd
